    {
        "content": "<p>Ah, good point. I think we can just assume/prove that the global Holder norms are bounded, but let me indeed check with my coauthors what the best solution is.</p>",
        "id": 509921490,
        "sender_full_name": "Floris van Doorn",
        "timestamp": 1743682234
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>A possible fix (with slightly worse constants, but otherwise the same statement): start with <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>φ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\varphi</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">φ</span></span></span></span> on the ball <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>z</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>R</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B(z, R)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.04398em;\">z</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>, extend it to a global Hölder function <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>φ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\varphi_1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">φ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> (with Hölder constant bounded by <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi>φ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mrow><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>z</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>R</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">4 ||\\varphi||_{B(z, R)}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.1052em;vertical-align:-0.3552em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">4∣∣</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">φ</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3448em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5198em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mopen mtight\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.04398em;\">z</span><span class=\"mpunct mtight\">,</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span><span class=\"mclose mtight\">)</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3552em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, using the analogue of <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=LipschitzOnWith.extend_real#doc\">docs#LipschitzOnWith.extend_real</a> for Hölder, and the fact that complex are two-dimensional so no bad loss). Then, use a cutoff function equal to <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span></span></span></span> on <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>z</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>R</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B(z, R)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.04398em;\">z</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">0</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span></span> outside of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>z</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B(z, 3R/2)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.04398em;\">z</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">3</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span><span class=\"mord\">/2</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> to truncate <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>φ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\varphi_1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">φ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> into a new function <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>φ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\varphi_2</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">φ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, still keeping good controls. The function <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>φ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\varphi_2</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">φ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is globally Hölder continuous and controlled. Then apply the regularization procedure to <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>φ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\varphi_2</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">φ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> instead of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>φ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\varphi</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">φ</span></span></span></span> (with parameter <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mn>2</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">t/2</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span><span class=\"mord\">/2</span></span></span></span> to make sure that the final function is still supported in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>z</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B(z, 2R)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.04398em;\">z</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>).</p>",
        "id": 509924026,
        "sender_full_name": "Sébastien Gouëzel",
        "timestamp": 1743682984
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh, that might be better, since that wouldn't affect any statements outside chapter 8 (besides some constants).</p>",
        "id": 509927058,
        "sender_full_name": "Floris van Doorn",
        "timestamp": 1743683732
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The cheapest fix would be to assume that <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>φ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\varphi</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">φ</span></span></span></span> is supported in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>z</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>R</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B(z, R/2)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.04398em;\">z</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span><span class=\"mord\">/2</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> in the statement. If that's enough for the applications, I mean.</p>",
        "id": 509927536,
        "sender_full_name": "Sébastien Gouëzel",
        "timestamp": 1743683833
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Forget about my fix above, it doesn't work. So the simplest thing is really to assume in Lemma 8.0.1 that the function is supported on B(z, R) but Hölder on B(z, 2R). And same thing for Proposition 2.0.5.</p>",
        "id": 510008695,
        "sender_full_name": "Sébastien Gouëzel",
        "timestamp": 1743704372
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Lars also replied that assuming it's Hölder on B(z, 2R) is probably the easiest fix. That does/should hold in the places where we apply Prop 2.0.5.</p>",
        "id": 510143264,
        "sender_full_name": "Floris van Doorn",
        "timestamp": 1743761619
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ok. I'll adapt the blueprint to that, tweak the current statement of Lemma 8.0.1, and prove Proposition 2.0.5 with that assumption, if that's ok with you.</p>",
        "id": 510155682,
        "sender_full_name": "Sébastien Gouëzel",
        "timestamp": 1743765385
    }
]